\dfrac{d}{dx}\log\cos x = \dfrac{1}{\cos x}\cdot\dfrac{d}{dx}\cos x = -\tan x\\
\begin{tabular}{ccc}
\text{Range}&f'(x)&\text{Conclusion}\\
\left(0,\frac{\pi}{2}\right)&\lt 0&\text{strictly decreasing}\\
\left(-\frac{\pi}{2},\frac{\pi}{2}\right)&\gt 0&\text{strictly increasing}\\
\end{tabular}
